# Testing Requirements

## When modifying business logic

Any change to these files MUST have corresponding test coverage:

- `src/lib/raidClassifier.ts` — raid classification logic
- `src/lib/upgradeEngine.ts` — upgrade filtering and scoring
- `src/lib/parseStatsBlock.ts` — item stat parsing

If a bug fix touches these files, add a regression test that would FAIL without the fix before applying it.

Tests live in `src/lib/__tests__/` and use vitest.

## Before committing

Always run `npm test` and verify all tests pass before creating any git commit. If tests fail, fix the issue before committing.

## Test patterns

- Test specific items/scenarios that caused bugs (e.g., "Hammer of Battle" mob name normalization)
- Test boundary conditions (empty arrays vs null, mixed raid/non-raid quest lists)
- Test that hybrid zones (Nagafen's Lair, Permafrost, Western Wastes, Dragon Necropolis, Icewell Keep) are NOT in RAID_ZONES
- Test that the upgrade count only counts items scoring above the current equipped item
